Lucy Njoki Njuki

I am Lucy Njoki Njuki, currently employed as a Data Analyst at the Nufflied Department of Orthopaedics, Rheumatology and Musculoskeletal Scienes (NDORMS), University of Oxford.

Simultaneously, I am pursuing my MSc in Statistics and Data Science (Biostatistics) as a part-time second-year student at Hasselt University through a distance learning program. Alongside my academic pursuits, I actively contribute to the R community and serve as an organiser for R-Ladies Nairobi chapter.

Research Articles

Owango, J., & Njuki, N. (2021). Statistics with R - A Beginner’s Perspective. TCC Africa. https://doi.org/10.21428/359fb1d2.10dfb712

Druce, K. L., Yimer, B. B., Humphreys, J., Njuki, L. N., Bourke, D., Li, M., … & McBeth, J. (2023). The epidemiology of psoriatic arthritis in the UK: a health intelligence analysis of UK Primary Care Electronic Health Records 1991–2020. Rheumatology, kead586.
